@Api_HostAddress = https://localhost:7266
@originAccountId = 4aa5fad7-a03c-4b59-a00d-fc0e0fe7374b
@destinationAccountId = 73fd7027-1677-457f-b7c3-e3d9476795e4
# @transactionId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@transactionId = c5e08a3f-8b21-45e2-9538-de76a9c812fb

### Health check basico
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/openapi/v1.json
Accept: application/json

### Conta de origem - massa de teste
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Conta Origem Teste",
  "document": "16670073607",
  "email": "origem.teste@festpay.com",
  "phone": "11999999999"
}

### Conta de destino - massa de teste
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Conta Destino Teste",
  "document": "39053344705",
  "email": "destino.teste@festpay.com",
  "phone": "11988888888"
}

### Listar contas para copiar os ids gerados
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts
Accept: application/json

### Desativar ou reativar conta por id
PATCH {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts/{{originAccountId}}
Accept: application/json

### Carregar saldo da conta de origem (Charge)
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts/{{originAccountId}}/charge
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 50.00
}

### Carregar saldo da conta de destino (Charge)
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/accounts/{{destinationAccountId}}/charge
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 200.00
}

### Criar transacao - massa happy path
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{destinationAccountId}}",
  "amount": 75.25
}

### Criar transacao duplicada (Anti-duplicidade) - deve falhar por 5 minutos
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{destinationAccountId}}",
  "amount": 75.25
}


### Criar transacao com valor decimal alternativo
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{destinationAccountId}}",
  "amount": 10.50
}

### Criar transacao invalida - mesma conta
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "amount": 10
}

### Criar transacao invalida - saldo insuficiente
POST {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originAccountId": "{{originAccountId}}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{{destinationAccountId}}",
  "amount": 999999.99
}

### Listar transacoes
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Accept: application/json

### Buscar transacao por id
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transactionId}}
Accept: application/json

### Cancelar transacao por id
PATCH {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transactionId}}/cancel
Accept: application/json

### Cancelar novamente para validar bloqueio de duplicidade
PATCH {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transactionId}}/cancel
Accept: application/json

### Buscar transacao cancelada por id
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transactionId}}
Accept: application/json

### Listar transacoes apos cancelamento
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions
Accept: application/json

### Consultar id inexistente
GET {{Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/transactions/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
Accept: application/json
